g.text: DP101 is a TFT LCD breakout adapter for the ER-TFT035-6 from BuyDisplay.com
DP101 Can be ordered from OshPark:
NOTE: The Teensy pin numbers on the schematic
correspond to the board's numbers NOT the Arduino pin numbers.
The Arduino pin numbers are listed in the name tag
of each pin on the schematic symbol for the Teensy 4.1 board.
ENC101 is the input wheel. I used a cheap 20 step per revolution
quadrature encoder with integrated switch. You can get
as fancy as you want and use a nicer, higher resolution
encoder here. I just didn't have one at the time and was
able to get the 20p/r to work well.
